law.text:
As used in KRS 216.750 to 216.780:
"Nursing home" means a facility which provides routine medical care in which physicians regularly visit patients, which provides nursing services and procedures employed in caring for the sick which require training, judgment, technical knowledge, and skills beyond that which the untrained person possesses, and which maintains complete records on patient care;
"Personal-care home" means a place devoted primarily to the maintenance and operation of facilities for the care of aged or invalid persons who do not require intensive care normally provided in a hospital or nursing home but who do require care in excess of room, board, and laundry;
"Fund" means the Nursing Home and Personal Care Home Loan Fund; and
"Secretary" means the secretary of the Cabinet for Health and Family Services.
